#: ../../../doc/en/doctest.rst:3
msgid "Doctest integration for modules and test files"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/doctest.rst:5
msgid ""
"By default all files matching the ``test*.txt`` pattern will be run through "
"the python standard ``doctest`` module.  You can change the pattern by "
"issuing::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/doctest.rst:9
msgid "pytest --doctest-glob='*.rst'"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/doctest.rst:11
msgid ""
"on the command line. Since version ``2.9``, ``--doctest-glob`` can be given "
"multiple times in the command-line."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/doctest.rst:16
msgid ""
"You can specify the encoding that will be used for those doctest files using "
"the ``doctest_encoding`` ini option:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/doctest.rst:19
msgid ""
"# content of pytest.ini\n"
"[pytest]\n"
"doctest_encoding = latin1"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/doctest.rst:25
msgid "The default encoding is UTF-8."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/doctest.rst:27
msgid ""
"You can also trigger running of doctests from docstrings in all python "
"modules (including regular python test modules)::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/doctest.rst:31
msgid "pytest --doctest-modules"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/doctest.rst:33
msgid ""
"You can make these changes permanent in your project by putting them into a "
"pytest.ini file like this:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/doctest.rst:36
msgid ""
"# content of pytest.ini\n"
"[pytest]\n"
"addopts = --doctest-modules"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/doctest.rst:42
msgid "If you then have a text file like this::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/doctest.rst:44
msgid ""
"# content of example.rst\n"
"\n"
"hello this is a doctest\n"
">>> x = 3\n"
">>> x\n"
"3"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/doctest.rst:51
msgid "and another like this::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/doctest.rst:53
msgid ""
"# content of mymodule.py\n"
"def something():\n"
"    \"\"\" a doctest in a docstring\n"
"    >>> something()\n"
"    42\n"
"    \"\"\"\n"
"    return 42"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/doctest.rst:61
msgid "then you can just invoke ``pytest`` without command line options::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/doctest.rst:63
msgid ""
"$ pytest\n"
"=========================== test session starts "
"============================\n"
"platform linux -- Python 3.x.y, pytest-3.x.y, py-1.x.y, pluggy-0.x.y\n"
"rootdir: $REGENDOC_TMPDIR, inifile: pytest.ini\n"
"collected 1 item\n"
"\n"
"mymodule.py .                                                        [100%]\n"
"\n"
"========================= 1 passed in 0.12 seconds ========================="
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/doctest.rst:73
msgid "It is possible to use fixtures using the ``getfixture`` helper::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/doctest.rst:75
msgid ""
"# content of example.rst\n"
">>> tmp = getfixture('tmpdir')\n"
">>> ...\n"
">>>"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/doctest.rst:80
msgid ""
"Also, :ref:`usefixtures` and :ref:`autouse` fixtures are supported when "
"executing text doctest files."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/doctest.rst:83
msgid ""
"The standard ``doctest`` module provides some setting flags to configure the "
"strictness of doctest tests. In pytest, you can enable those flags using the "
"configuration file. To make pytest ignore trailing whitespaces and ignore "
"lengthy exception stack traces you can just write:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/doctest.rst:88
msgid ""
"[pytest]\n"
"doctest_optionflags= NORMALIZE_WHITESPACE IGNORE_EXCEPTION_DETAIL"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/doctest.rst:93
msgid ""
"pytest also introduces new options to allow doctests to run in Python 2 and "
"Python 3 unchanged:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/doctest.rst:96
msgid ""
"``ALLOW_UNICODE``: when enabled, the ``u`` prefix is stripped from unicode "
"strings in expected doctest output."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/doctest.rst:99
msgid ""
"``ALLOW_BYTES``: when enabled, the ``b`` prefix is stripped from byte "
"strings in expected doctest output."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/doctest.rst:102
msgid ""
"As with any other option flag, these flags can be enabled in ``pytest.ini`` "
"using the ``doctest_optionflags`` ini option:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/doctest.rst:105
msgid ""
"[pytest]\n"
"doctest_optionflags = ALLOW_UNICODE ALLOW_BYTES"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/doctest.rst:111
msgid ""
"Alternatively, it can be enabled by an inline comment in the doc test "
"itself::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/doctest.rst:114
msgid ""
"# content of example.rst\n"
">>> get_unicode_greeting()  # doctest: +ALLOW_UNICODE\n"
"'Hello'"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/doctest.rst:118
msgid ""
"By default, pytest would report only the first failure for a given doctest.  "
"If you want to continue the test even when you have failures, do::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/doctest.rst:121
msgid "pytest --doctest-modules --doctest-continue-on-failure"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/doctest.rst:127
msgid "The 'doctest_namespace' fixture"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/doctest.rst:131
msgid ""
"The ``doctest_namespace`` fixture can be used to inject items into the "
"namespace in which your doctests run. It is intended to be used within your "
"own fixtures to provide the tests that use them with context."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/doctest.rst:135
msgid ""
"``doctest_namespace`` is a standard ``dict`` object into which you place the "
"objects you want to appear in the doctest namespace::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/doctest.rst:138
msgid ""
"# content of conftest.py\n"
"import numpy\n"
"@pytest.fixture(autouse=True)\n"
"def add_np(doctest_namespace):\n"
"    doctest_namespace['np'] = numpy"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/doctest.rst:144
msgid "which can then be used in your doctests directly::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/doctest.rst:146
msgid ""
"# content of numpy.py\n"
"def arange():\n"
"    \"\"\"\n"
"    >>> a = np.arange(10)\n"
"    >>> len(a)\n"
"    10\n"
"    \"\"\"\n"
"    pass"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/doctest.rst:157
msgid "Output format"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/doctest.rst:161
msgid ""
"You can change the diff output format on failure for your doctests by using "
"one of standard doctest modules format in options (see :data:`python:doctest."
"REPORT_UDIFF`, :data:`python:doctest.REPORT_CDIFF`, :data:`python:doctest."
"REPORT_NDIFF`, :data:`python:doctest.REPORT_ONLY_FIRST_FAILURE`)::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/doctest.rst:166
msgid ""
"pytest --doctest-modules --doctest-report none\n"
"pytest --doctest-modules --doctest-report udiff\n"
"pytest --doctest-modules --doctest-report cdiff\n"
"pytest --doctest-modules --doctest-report ndiff\n"
"pytest --doctest-modules --doctest-report only_first_failure"
msgstr ""
